function minDifference(nums) {
    let size = nums.length;
    if (size < 5) return 0;

    nums.sort((a, b) => a - b);

    return Math.min(nums[size-1] - nums[3], nums[size-2] - nums[2], nums[size-3] - nums[1], nums[size-4] - nums[0]);
}
```

    1. First, we check if the array size is less than 5. If yes, we can make all elements equal in at most 3 moves, so the minimum difference will be 0.
2. Sort the given array.
3. We need to change at most 3 smallest or largest elements. We have four combinations of this. We could change:
    - 3 largest elements (1 smallest)
    - 2 largest elements and 1 smallest element (2 smallest)
    - 1 largest element and 2 smallest elements (3 smallest)
    - 3 smallest elements (4 smallest)
4. Calculate the difference for all four combinations and return the minimum difference.

